  <!-- Video Types That Drive Installs -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-slate-50 dark:from-slate-800 dark:to-slate-900">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-primary mb-2">The Playbook</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">The 5 Video Types That Drive Shopify App Installs</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted mt-4 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Not every video format converts. These five map directly to the searches merchants make while deciding which app to install.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold text-primary">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">"Best [Category] Apps for Shopify" Roundups</h3>
            <p class="text-muted">This is the highest-intent search in the app ecosystem. A merchant typing it has a problem, a budget, and a plan to install something this week. A roundup that ranks for your category owns the shortlist for every merchant who makes that search. Include real alternatives and be honest about tradeoffs. The credibility is what converts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold text-primary">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Comparison Videos: [Your App] vs [Competitor]</h3>
            <p class="text-muted">By the time a merchant searches a direct comparison, the decision is down to two or three apps. A side-by-side that covers pricing, setup time, and support quality wins the tiebreak. If you skip this video, a competitor or an affiliate will make it instead, and they will frame the comparison their way.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold text-primary">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Problem-Solution Tutorials</h3>
            <p class="text-muted">Merchants search the problem, not your app name: "how to reduce cart abandonment on Shopify", "how to recover lost checkout revenue". A tutorial that genuinely teaches the fix, then shows your app as the fastest way to implement it, converts a viewer who did not know your app existed ten minutes earlier.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold text-primary">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">"Is [App] Worth It" Reviews</h3>
            <p class="text-muted">These viewers are sitting on your pricing page with the tab still open. One unresolved question stands between them and the install button: does this app justify the monthly fee? A video that addresses cost directly, shows the app running in a real store, and names who should not install it turns hesitant researchers into trials.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold text-primary">5</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Setup and Workflow Walkthroughs</h3>
            <p class="text-muted">A walkthrough captures "[app name] tutorial" and "[app name] setup" searches, reduces churn for new users, and quietly reassures pre-install researchers that onboarding will not be painful. It is the least glamorous format and one of the most consistent converters, because everyone watching is already deep in your funnel.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/30 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-700 rounded-xl p-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="font-semibold text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-100 mb-2">Where to start:</p>
        <p class="text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-100 mb-0">If you only produce one video this quarter, make the roundup for your category. It targets the single highest-intent query in your market, and every other format eventually routes traffic toward it. Comparisons and problem-solution tutorials come next. Walkthroughs can wait until install volume justifies them.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

