      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 md:p-10 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">Every video in this system is faceless. A script written from keyword research, a screen recording of a real Shopify store and your app's admin, and a voiceover. No studio, no presenter, no filming days.</p>

          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">A typical video runs 6 to 12 minutes. Long enough to satisfy the search intent properly, short enough that a busy merchant finishes it. Behind each one sits the real work: query selection, a competitive review of what already ranks, a script that answers the search directly, screen capture, an edit, and a title and thumbnail built for the query rather than for clicks.</p>

          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">Plan on the first month being the slowest. Query research and demo store setup happen once. Every video after that reuses the foundation, which is why the cadence holds without burning anyone out.</p>

          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">At 4 videos per month, you build a library of roughly 48 videos in year one. Each one targets a different buying-intent query. That is the compounding mechanism behind the experiment above: the library keeps ranking while you keep adding to it.</p>

          <div class="my-6 pl-6 border-l-4 border-primary/50 bg-primary/5 py-4 pr-4 rounded-r-lg">
            <p class="text-lg mb-0">Your team's involvement stays small by design. Product context at the start, a demo store or sandbox access, and an approval pass on each script. In practice that is an hour or two per month, not a content operation you have to staff.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

